    "Given a row of tabular data x = (x 0,..., x p-1) ∈ R p, its DFT is defined as y = DFT(x):= (y 0,..., y p-1) ∈ C p where y t =foot_0 √ p p-1 n=0x n e -i 2π p tn for each t = 0,..., p -1, The inverse DFT (IDFT) is given by x = IDFT(y) ∈ R p where x n = 1 √ p p-1 k=0 y k e i 2π p kn for each n = 0,..., p -1.",
